induced sensitivity and selectivity in otft sensors via calixarene layers bao research group stanford university home people current alumni new member research research topics archived news wikilab lab members only publications press contact us visitors the introduction of a ultra thin calix n arene layer onto the surface of a top contact otft results in a dramatic increase in sensitivity and selectivity of small molecular analytes the shape and size of the calix n arene cavity can be used to tune the sensor selectivity importantly the incorporation of the sensory layer does not influence device performance thus enabling integration within commercial otft devices link http www3 interscience wiley com journal 123341740 abstract copyright 2009 2011 all rights reserved credits bao group benjamin tee soumen barmen logo by benjamin tee
